social_posts.post_text: In 2006 I released an album on my label by a band called Gil Mantera’s Party Dream. Today a documentary about the band is being released. I highly recommend checking it out. Party Dream the movie.

I get asked all the time who my favorite drummers are. My answer is most always john bonham, bill ward, Russel Simins, and Jeremiah Green. In the last six years I was lucky enough to become friends with him. Tour with him. The most profound influence on my drumming is from him. I remember listening to modest mouse before I really even played drums and thinking if I played drums I would play like him. He lost a battle to cancer yesterday. He was loved by all that met him and he touched all his friends deeply and profoundly. Thank you for everything Jeremiah.

social_posts.post_text: R.I.P. Tom Verlaine

Rest In Peace John Adams. John woke up one day in 1973 and for some odd reason decided to take his drum to the bleachers at municipal stadium. He beat the drum from that point on for every @cleguardians home game (missing only 40 odd games) until his health declined in late 2020. John was a true Ohio eccentric and a wonderful person. He will be greatly missed and I feel very lucky to have gotten to sit with him for a game. 🙏
